Avoid saturated colors.

---

# Component Guidelines

Create reusable components.

Examples:

Navbar

Mega Menu

Hero

Section Header

Department Card

Faculty Card

Research Card

News Card

Statistics

Timeline

Gallery

CTA

Breadcrumb

Footer

All components should follow a consistent design system.

---

# Motion Guidelines

Animations should enhance usability rather than distract.

Allowed:

- Fade In
- Slide Up
- Scale
- Stagger
- Counter Animation
- Hover Elevation
- Button Ripple
- Image Reveal
- Smooth Page Transition
- Parallax

Avoid:

- Heavy GSAP timelines
- Scroll hijacking
- Constant floating animations
- Cursor trails
- Overly dramatic effects

Motion should feel subtle and premium.

---

# UX Principles

Prioritize:

Clear navigation

Fast information discovery

Accessibility

Responsive layouts

Readable typography

Large touch targets

Logical content hierarchy

Excellent mobile experience

---

# Performance

Target:

95+ Lighthouse

Semantic HTML

SEO-friendly structure

Lazy-loaded images

Optimized fonts

Minimal JavaScript

Accessibility score above 95

---

# Technology

Next.js App Router

TypeScript

Tailwind CSS

Framer Motion

GSAP (only where necessary)

Lenis (optional)

React Hook Form

Zod

Shadcn UI (only if needed)

---

# Development Principles

Build reusable sections.

Never duplicate layouts.

Prefer reusable templates for:

Departments

Faculty

Research

Programs

News

Events

Gallery

All data should be easily replaceable with CMS or API content in the future.

---

# Code Quality

Write production-ready code.

Use clean component architecture.

Follow TypeScript best practices.

Avoid unnecessary dependencies.

Ensure accessibility and responsive behavior by default.

---

# Goal

Deliver a premium institutional website that feels like a modern international engineering university while preserving the strengths of the Univet template.

The result should look bespoke, not like an off-the-shelf theme.